rComments: Took for EAS210* If you pay close attention in this course and do lots of work outside of lecture/tutorial, I am sure you will do fine. However this past year she seemed only half interested in teaching. Instead of challenging students she would just automatically give answers for us to recite in unison. Counterproductive for a language course.

rComments: Same prof who taught at York for Korean, but don't take this class lightly. This is not  a bird and if you don't put in a lot of time, say goodbye to your GPA. Take EAS110 or EAS210 for bird. Only thing I did not like was the final exam; very long and difficult exam that brought everyone marks down.

rComments: OMG the final exam, like for real. What was that?? I was going to this prof 55 rating for everything, but the exam wtf. I was getting high 80s in this course before the final exam, but the final exam was ridiciously hard. Over 10 pages, with lots of questions AND 2 essay questions WITHIN 2 HOURS. Very hard and long exam, horrible ending....

This class is okay. The only problems was that there are too many assignmentswork in this class. Quizzes every week along with presentations, book reports, essays etc.. If your Korean isn't strong, you will spend alot of hours on work. ALSO, she makes you talk on the spot with questions, so be PREPARED to talk. Plus you can't skip bc of quizzes..
